Rabé was portrayed by Brazilian actress Cristina da Silva in the 1999 film Star Wars: Episode I The Phantom Menace, the first installment of the Star Wars prequel trilogy. The character, although unnamed in the movie itself, was identified as Rabé in the credits.

metadata.content:
# Augara Jowil - Behind the scenes[]

Augara Jowil was created for the May 19, 1999 prequel trilogy film, Star Wars: Episode I The Phantom Menace, but was first mentioned prior to the film's release in the title of the track "Augie's Great Municipal March" on the film's soundtrack, which was released on May 4. In the current Star Wars canon, the character's full name was used in Star Wars - The Official Magazine 90, which was released in 2018. Jowil's full name originated in the Star Wars Legends continuity, where it was first used in an entry for the character written by Chad Finke and published as part of the Hyperspace feature "What's The Story?" on StarWars.com.
metadata.title: Augara Jowil

metadata.content:
# Augara Jowil - Behind the scenes[]

The character of Augara Jowil first appeared in George Lucas' 1999 film Star Wars: Episode I The Phantom Menace as a background character late in the film. She was later identified and elaborated on by Chad Finke, via StarWars.com's Hyperspace feature "What's The Story?" Finke's entry, published in the Databank, identified the Gungan as "Augie" from the track title "Augie's Great Municipal Band"—the final track on the original soundtrack of The Phantom Menace. The entry was added to the Databank on January 12, 2007. Augara later received an entry in the 2008 reference book The Complete Star Wars Encyclopedia, though her entry misspelled her first name "Augarra."
metadata.title: Augara Jowil
